--====================================================
-- WEBHOOK MONITOR v4.1
-- Multi-route Discord webhook monitor for Roblox
--====================================================
--
-- ┌─ QUICK START ───────────────────────────────────┐
-- │  1. Run the script — a setup screen appears.    │
-- │  2. Paste your Discord webhook URL and save.    │
-- │  3. Open the "webhooks" tab to add more routes. │
-- │  4. Each route can point to a different channel.│
-- └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
--
-- ┌─ HOW TO ADD A NEW INFO VALUE TO TRACK ──────────┐
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 1 — Decide if it needs its own webhook     │
-- │    • Same channel as another module? Reuse that  │
-- │      route key (e.g. "tokens", "players").       │
-- │    • Want a dedicated Discord channel for it?    │
-- │      Add a new key to Config.Webhooks below,     │
-- │      then enter the URL in the "webhooks" tab.   │
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 2 — Add a module entry to Config.Modules   │
-- │    MyThing = {                                   │
-- │      enabled    = true,                          │
-- │      label      = "My Thing",   -- shown in UI  │
-- │      color      = 0xRRGGBB,     -- embed color  │
-- │      webhookKey = "tokens",     -- route to use │
-- │    },                                            │
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 3 — Find the value in the game's GUI       │
-- │    Use the debug probe in the Players tab to     │
-- │    verify the path works before writing code.    │
-- │    Pattern: PlayerGui -> ScreenGui -> Frame ->   │
-- │    TextLabel (use :FindFirstChild("Name") chain) │
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 4 — Watch it with GetPropertyChangedSignal │
-- │    label:GetPropertyChangedSignal("Text")        │
-- │      :Connect(function()                         │
-- │        if Config.Modules.MyThing.enabled then    │
-- │          sendTo("tokens", buildEmbed({ ... }))   │
-- │        end                                       │
-- │      end)                                        │
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 5 — Send the initial value right away      │
-- │    After finding the label, call sendTo() once   │
-- │    with the current .Text so Discord always has  │
-- │    a baseline even before any change fires.      │
-- │    (See setupTokenWatcher for a full example.)   │
-- │                                                  │
-- │  STEP 6 — Call your setup function at the bottom │
-- │    Add setupMyThing() near the end of the file   │
-- │    alongside setupTokenWatcher() etc.            │
-- └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

